<hl>
<seg id=1> August's Retail Index Fell 8.3% in Comparison with Last Year </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> The retail index of August fell 8.3% in comparison with last year, and it has already been the straight 12th drop. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Since September of 1997, when the retail index was comparable to the previous year, it has fallen steadily without increase, which indicates that the local retail industry is still struggling in the low tide. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Compared with that of this July, the retail index has dropped by 8.3%. </seg>
<seg id=5> If automobiles are not included, the index has dropped by 3.9%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> According to the numbers provided by the Statistics Bureau, almost all retail activity in August was calm. </seg>
<seg id=7> Automobile sale amounts rocketed by 41.4%, but fell again by 19.9% in August. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Other retail industries with shrinking transactions include: furniture and household wares(8%), textile and personal articles (7.8%), department store and supermarkets (2.6%) ну gasoline stations (1.3%) and grocery stores (0.3%). </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> On the other hand, the restaurant index dropped by 4.5% in comparison with that of last year, which is a continuous 7 month drop since February 1998. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> But, in comparison with July, the dietetic index rose a small degree to 1.4%. </seg>
<seg id=11> The money people spent on eating and drinking has increased from 245 million to 248 million yuan since July. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> The related increase owes much to its drive by the 6.6% rise in dining out. </seg>
<seg id=13> The sales volume at other dining places, aside from restaurants, has also increased by 2.5%. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=14> The retail index and dietetic index are numbers publicized by the Statistics Bureau monthly, which are designed to inform about the short term behavior of the retail and dietetic industries nationally. </seg>
</p>
